The '''Ubese raider armor''', also known as '''Ubese armor''', was a type of [[Armor/Legends|armor]] usually worn by [[Ubese/Legends|Ubese]] trackers.

==Description==
Ubese armors offered a high degree of protection against energy-based weapons like [[Blaster/Legends|blasters]] but lesser protection from kinetic damage.<ref name="SWG:CU" /> A complete armor set consisted of a [[Helmet/Legends|helmet]], a shirt, a [[Ogygian cloak/Legends|jacket]]<ref name="SWG" /> with impact armor for the neck and chest, chest-mounted [[Comlink/Legends|comlink]] and [[Ubese clan belt-clasp/Legends|Ubese clan belt-clasp]],<ref name="TVD" /> left & right bracer,<ref name="SWG" /> [[Glove spikes/Legends|spiked]]<ref name="TVD" /> [[Glove/Legends|gloves]], a [[Bandolier/Legends|bandolier]]<ref name="SWG" /> with [[projectile detonator]] and [[ammo pouch]]es,<ref name="TVD" /> [[Shata leather pants/Legends|pants]] and [[Ubese boots/Legends|boots]]. It was available in several different colors.<ref name="SWG" /> The armor was ideally suited for upgrades and modifications.<ref name="GFT:PG">''[[Gundark's Fantastic Technology: Personal Gear]]''</ref>

[[File:Ubese_Gloves.jpg|thumb|left|150px|A helmet and a pair of Ubese gloves.]]
The helmet featured a [[flash guard visor]],<ref name="GFT:PG" /> a [[NiteSite infrared motion sensor]],<ref name="TEGtWaT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref> a [[Targeting laser/Legends|targeting laser]], a [[vision-plus scanner]], an [[Audio sensor/Legends|audio pickup]], a [[Broadband antenna/Legends|broadband antenna]], a [[Speech scrambler/Legends|speech scrambler]].<ref name="TVD" /> The headgear also contained an [[enviro filter]] designed to filtrate toxic fumes and maintain a [[Atmosphere/Legends#Type II atmospheres|Type II atmosphere]] for Ubese traveling throughout [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. For non-Ubese users, it was possible to adapt the helmet to accept a [[Type I enviro-filter]] but the modification reduced the reliability of the seal.<ref name="GFT:PG" />

==History==
{{Quote|They belonged to Boushh, an Ubese bounty hunter. Boushh was quite good at the trade. He did a lot of contract work for Black Sun. He&hellip; retired recently.|[[Guri]], giving [[Boushh/Legends|Boushh's]] outfit to [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]]|<ref name="SOTE novel">[[Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire (novel)|''Star Wars: Shadows of the Empire'' novel]]</ref>}}
During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], Ubese armors became popular among [[Spacer/Legends|spacers]].<ref name="SWG" /> In addition, a number of [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunters]] affiliated with the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] used to wear this kind of armor.<ref name="GB">''[[Star Wars: Galactic Battlegrounds]]''</ref> The armor was also worn by [[Sith Shadows|Sith Shadow]] warriors.<ref name="SWGTCG">{{SWGTCG|set=Agents of Deception|cardname=Sith Shadow Warrior}}</ref>

The bounty hunter [[Boushh/Legends|Boushh]] was an individual who wore an Ubese armor. That particular suit was also used by [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]], when attempting to [[Siege of Jabba's Palace|rescue]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] from [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]].<ref name="TVD" />

